				<h2>Question 1</h2>
			</div>
			<div id="question">
				<p>If you roll two dice and add the values on the dice together, what is the probability of rolling an even number?</p>
			</div>

			<div id="answer_check_div">
				<input name="input_ans_1" id="input_ans_1" type="text">
				<input type="button" name="check_ans_button" value="Check Answer" onclick="check_ans_1()"/>

				<div id="correct_1"  style="display:none;" class="answer_list" > 
					<p>Correct</p>
				</div>

				<div id="incorrect_1"  style="display:none;" class="answer_list" > 
					<p>Incorrect</p>
				</div>
			</div>
	

			<div id="display_answer">
				<input type="button" name="answer" value="Answer" onclick="show_ans_1()" />

				<div id="answer_1"  style="display:none;" class="answer_list" > 
					<p>For the sum to be even, the numbers on the two dice mus both be even or odd. If one dice is even and the other odd the sum will be odd. Therefore the probability is:
		    P(odd number, odd number) + P(even number, even number) = 0.5x0.5+0.5x0.5 = 0.5</p>
				</div>
			</div>

